  "doc_id": "223",
  "text": "The damage-free nature of the XFEL data is extremely attractive and it should be possible, in principle, to collect data from crystals with dimensions as small as about 100 nanometers [CITATION_1] . However, millions of crystals were needed for these experiments, and reducing this number will be a significant challenge. Moreover, access to XFEL facilities is limited. Since transmission electron cryomicroscopes are available in many laboratories, whereas there are only a handful of XFELs in the world, one possible application of the electron diffraction approach pioneered by the Janelia Farm team would be to pre-screen samples so that only the most promising are investigated further at XFEL facilities.",
  "correct_citation": {
